2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed framework can be applied to robotics applications where multiple sensors or agents are involved in tracking and navigation tasks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the problem of distributed estimation and fusion, which is a common problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a machine learning technique (particle filter) for distributed estimation and fusion, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a distributed algorithm that requires communication between nodes, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
